At age 18, Ronaldo made his first senior appearance for Portugal in a 1–0 victory over Kazakhstan on 20 August 2003.[280] He was subsequently called up for UEFA Euro 2004, held in his home country, and scored his first international goal in a 2–1 group stage loss to eventual champions Greece.[281] After converting his penalty in a shoot-out against England in the quarter-finals,[282] he helped Portugal reach the final by scoring the opening goal in a 2–1 win over the Netherlands.[283] He was featured in the team of the tournament, having provided two assists in addition to his two goals.[284]
